1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:37,920
=Episode 15=

3
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,520
Hello, Ms. Ding.

4
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:41,330
Is your right hand

5
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:42,889
any better?

6
00:01:42,890 --> 00:01:43,449
I'm sorry.

7
00:01:43,450 --> 00:01:46,130
I burned you when you were at my firm.

8
00:01:46,290 --> 00:01:48,360
I promised to reimburse
your medical fees.

9
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:50,520
Show me the receipt.

10
00:01:53,810 --> 00:01:55,850
(Family Court)
Plaintiff's lawyer, this is unrelated...

11
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:57,210
Let her ask.

12
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:59,330
Plaintiff's lawyer, continue.

13
00:01:59,890 --> 00:02:01,080
Ms. Ding.

14
00:02:01,450 --> 00:02:02,569
I misspoke.

15
00:02:02,570 --> 00:02:04,330
I remember it was the left hand.

16
00:02:07,530 --> 00:02:08,249
Judge Shen.

17
00:02:08,250 --> 00:02:10,840
I have reason to suspect
that the plaintiff is not my client.

18
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,039
Your Honor!

19
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:12,889
She's lying.

20
00:02:12,890 --> 00:02:15,009
This lawyer is disrupting the court.

21
00:02:15,010 --> 00:02:16,039
Aren't you going to stop her?

22
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:17,319
Ding Yajing.

23
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,289
Date of birth?

24
00:02:18,290 --> 00:02:20,330
March 9, 1995.

25
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,759
What's your Chinese zodiac sign?

26
00:02:23,760 --> 00:02:24,729
The Pig.

27
00:02:24,730 --> 00:02:25,639
And your lunar birthday?

28
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:27,359
I never go by the lunar calendar.

29
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,849
My birthday is March 9.

30
00:02:28,850 --> 00:02:30,730
Who was your university chancellor?

31
00:02:32,290 --> 00:02:34,960
I studied accounting
at Tianhai University.

32
00:02:37,320 --> 00:02:39,610
I asked for the chancellor's name.

33
00:02:39,690 --> 00:02:40,920
It's...

34
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:53,919
The name is...

35
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:55,079
Miss,

36
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:56,319
I have reasons to suspect

37
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:58,210
you aren't the plaintiff, Ding Yajing.

38
00:03:00,850 --> 00:03:01,849
Ms. Qin.

39
00:03:01,850 --> 00:03:03,240
Hello, Ms. Ding.

40
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,050
Ding Yawei?

41
00:03:11,410 --> 00:03:13,210
Ding Yawei, what is going on?

42
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:15,199
Why are you with Cheng Kuiyuan?

43
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,920
Talk to me!

44
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:18,969
Look at me and start talking!

45
00:03:18,970 --> 00:03:20,319
What's the deal with you two?

46
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:21,639
Explain yourself right now!

47
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,960
Ding Yawei!

48
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:26,199
Not those. Don't pack those shoes.

49
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:26,639
Why not?

50
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,919
Take the black ones.

51
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:30,170
The ones with the cracks. Not these.

52
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,289
It's just for the hospital.

53
00:03:32,290 --> 00:03:34,210
We'll toss them afterwards anyway.

54
00:03:34,850 --> 00:03:37,169
Why are you worrying about this?

55
00:03:37,170 --> 00:03:39,599
Can we just focus for a second?

56
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:41,249
We're on a tight budget, remember?

57
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:42,289
Look,

58
00:03:42,290 --> 00:03:44,799
Dr. Bai has amazing reviews online.

59
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:47,039
They say his cosmetic stitches
are incredible.

60
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:49,120
You won't even see a scar.

61
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:49,729
Really?

62
00:03:49,730 --> 00:03:50,960
Yeah.

63
00:03:51,730 --> 00:03:53,120
I was thinking,

64
00:03:53,690 --> 00:03:56,490
after the surgery,
we'll hire a caregiver.

65
00:03:56,690 --> 00:03:59,490
One caregiver covers a few patients,

66
00:03:59,570 --> 00:04:00,800
so it's not expensive.

67
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:03,479
You can just call her
if you need anything.

68
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:06,170
That way, she isn't hovering over you.

69
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,569
And it won't affect your work.

70
00:04:07,570 --> 00:04:09,450
You can keep doing your thing.

71
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,249
Don't keep all those people

72
00:04:11,250 --> 00:04:12,799
waiting on their lawsuits.

73
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,210
What do you think?

74
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:16,570
Honey?

75
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,759
I want to talk to you about something.

76
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:20,889
Go ahead.

77
00:04:20,890 --> 00:04:22,960
Can we wait a bit

78
00:04:23,810 --> 00:04:25,160
for this surgery?

79
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,040
Why?

80
00:04:34,450 --> 00:04:35,399
Yeah.

81
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,079
I don't think
it's that important either.

82
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,930
We can't let it get in the way
of Nian's studies abroad.

83
00:04:40,930 --> 00:04:43,040
That's not what I meant.

84
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:45,600
Maybe we can

85
00:04:45,610 --> 00:04:46,960
find a different doctor?

86
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:49,450
But this doctor is fine.

87
00:04:51,010 --> 00:04:53,570
Yeah, Dr. Bai is decent enough.

88
00:04:53,810 --> 00:04:56,010
But this is just a crazy coincidence.

89
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:58,079
Dr. Bai is in a lawsuit in our court.

90
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,370
Did you know that?

91
00:05:00,690 --> 00:05:02,570
The case is sitting right on my desk.

92
00:05:07,050 --> 00:05:08,600
I've looked over the file.

93
00:05:09,890 --> 00:05:11,609
The facts are black and white.

94
00:05:11,610 --> 00:05:12,889
As the presiding judge, I don't have

95
00:05:12,890 --> 00:05:14,159
much discretion here.

96
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:16,330
I'd likely grant his claims anyway.

97
00:05:17,130 --> 00:05:18,449
But with this personal connection,

98
00:05:18,450 --> 00:05:19,959
it's hard to explain away.

99
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:20,689
Exactly.

100
00:05:20,690 --> 00:05:22,839
Let's find someone else
to avoid any suspicion.

101
00:05:22,840 --> 00:05:24,040
Okay?

102
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:26,770
Forget it.

103
00:05:26,810 --> 00:05:29,370
I'm not doing the surgery at all.

104
00:05:29,690 --> 00:05:32,129
Switch hospitals, switch doctors...

105
00:05:32,130 --> 00:05:34,840
Who knows what issues
the next doctor will have?

106
00:05:35,570 --> 00:05:37,199
Honey,

107
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,080
don't say things you don't mean.

108
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,129
You have to have this surgery.

109
00:05:41,130 --> 00:05:42,449
And I refuse to believe

110
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:43,929
that in a city as big as Tianhai,

111
00:05:43,930 --> 00:05:45,720
he's the only expert available.

112
00:05:46,610 --> 00:05:47,839
I promise you,

113
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:49,369
soon,

114
00:05:49,370 --> 00:05:50,489
I will find a doctor

115
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:52,570
even better than Dr. Bai.

116
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:53,609
Trust me.

117
00:05:53,610 --> 00:05:55,049
In all our years of marriage,

118
00:05:55,050 --> 00:05:57,520
have I ever broken a promise to you?

119
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:11,640
It was obvious Ms. Qin
was getting suspicious.

120
00:06:12,050 --> 00:06:13,720
Something felt off to me, too.

121
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:16,640
I've seen fake divorces
where people are polite,

122
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:19,160
but never a real one
where they're both this happy.

123
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:20,600
So I bluffed.

124
00:06:20,890 --> 00:06:23,210
When she started stammering,

125
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:24,890
I knew I had her.

126
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:26,759
Ms. Qin finally got a hold of

127
00:06:26,760 --> 00:06:28,569
the real plaintiff, Ding Yajing.

128
00:06:28,570 --> 00:06:29,960
And get this.

129
00:06:30,810 --> 00:06:32,759
The imposter's name

130
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:34,690
is Ding Yawei.

131
00:06:34,930 --> 00:06:37,449
She's Ding Yajing's
identical twin sister.

132
00:06:37,450 --> 00:06:40,839
She's been living off her sister for years.

133
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:43,370
She was in cahoots with the defendant.

134
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:44,719
She actually

135
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,759
stole the plaintiff's phone,

136
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:49,009
messaged the lawyer
to change the hearing time,

137
00:06:49,010 --> 00:06:50,609
and then showed up

138
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:52,279
for the online trial!

139
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:54,040
My goodness, what a mess.

140
00:06:54,610 --> 00:06:56,009
Sounds like you and Ms. Qin

141
00:06:56,010 --> 00:06:58,160
actually make a pretty good team.

142
00:06:59,570 --> 00:07:01,959
That's just because I'm brilliant.

143
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,810
I deliver results with
everyone I work with.

144
00:07:05,610 --> 00:07:06,839
True enough.

145
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:08,010
Master,

146
00:07:08,610 --> 00:07:10,370
Don't use that sincere tone with me.

147
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,640
I'd feel better
if you just chewed me out.

148
00:07:13,450 --> 00:07:14,930
Have I ever chewed you out?

149
00:07:18,610 --> 00:07:19,810
I was kidding.

150
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,720
I'm sorry.

151
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:24,249
Master, why are you being so serious?

152
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:25,770
I was really just joking.

153
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,199
To be honest,

154
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,249
I once saw you

155
00:07:28,250 --> 00:07:29,929
as a product of a legal dynasty,

156
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:32,400
an assembly-line exam machine.

157
00:07:32,490 --> 00:07:34,519
No empathy, no sense of responsibility,

158
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,960
and always stuck-up.

159
00:07:36,010 --> 00:07:38,449
Just putting in your time
until you could bail.

160
00:07:38,450 --> 00:07:40,010
Regarding those charges,

161
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,719
other than being stuck-up,

162
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:43,250
I plead not guilty.

163
00:07:43,370 --> 00:07:46,400
That's mostly because I'm tall.

164
00:07:47,810 --> 00:07:49,129
Not just the height.

165
00:07:49,130 --> 00:07:52,279
You've got the brains,
the charm, and the talent.

166
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:53,930
Good-looking and kind-hearted, too.

167
00:07:54,010 --> 00:07:55,489
"Flower of the Family Court."

168
00:07:55,490 --> 00:07:57,840
And to Fei,
you're like the legendary Nezha.

169
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,370
Shen Xiezhi is actually pretty good.

170
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:03,519
In court today,

171
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:04,369
he fired off

172
00:08:04,370 --> 00:08:06,080
a string of questions with us watching.

173
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,480
Out of nowhere, he asked her,

174
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:10,810
"So, who was
your university chancellor?"

175
00:08:11,010 --> 00:08:13,040
She couldn't even get a word out.

176
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:16,129
I immediately video-called
the real Ding Yajing.

177
00:08:16,130 --> 00:08:17,159
Guess who

178
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:19,160
the imposter was?

179
00:08:19,690 --> 00:08:22,570
Look at you, Sherlock.
I can't believe you figured it out.

180
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:23,639
Waitress!

181
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:25,489
A glass of warm water for me, please.

182
00:08:25,490 --> 00:08:26,369
Sure.

183
00:08:26,370 --> 00:08:27,759
Oh, and I have more good news.

184
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:30,250
My channel just got more followers.

185
00:08:30,570 --> 00:08:31,930
Thirteen of them!

186
00:08:32,010 --> 00:08:32,889
Once I get

187
00:08:32,890 --> 00:08:34,129
all the case files organized

188
00:08:34,130 --> 00:08:35,799
and post them online,

189
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:37,919
I might actually
become a micro-influencer.

190
00:08:37,920 --> 00:08:38,639
Not bad, right?

191
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,330
Ms. Qin, here's your water.

192
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:42,000
Thank you.

193
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:45,609
Don't you think

194
00:08:45,610 --> 00:08:46,369
Ms. Ding now owes me

195
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:47,930
a huge bonus for this?

196
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:49,679
Wait.

197
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:50,089
Hold on.

198
00:08:50,090 --> 00:08:52,080
It's Ms. Ding. She's calling.

199
00:08:52,610 --> 00:08:52,919
Okay.

200
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:54,410
Yeah, just get over here quickly.

201
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:00,799
Ms. Ding?

202
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,489
What kind of lawyer

203
00:09:01,490 --> 00:09:04,170
can't even recognize her own client?

204
00:09:04,560 --> 00:09:05,969
I am so sorry, Ms. Ding.

205
00:09:05,970 --> 00:09:07,570
Please, try to stay calm.

206
00:09:08,210 --> 00:09:10,679
It was my mistake
for not realizing it sooner, but...

207
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:11,489
Well,

208
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:13,369
this has never happened before.

209
00:09:13,370 --> 00:09:14,559
I couldn't have anticipated this.

210
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:15,919
If you're this incompetent as a lawyer,

211
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,810
what are you even doing?

212
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:19,000
Look...

213
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:20,369
She is your biological

214
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:22,129
identical twin, isn't she?

215
00:09:22,130 --> 00:09:23,609
You never mentioned to me

216
00:09:23,610 --> 00:09:25,210
that you even had a twin sister.

217
00:09:25,490 --> 00:09:26,759
I really couldn't tell.

218
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:29,120
What kind of nonsense
are you spewing now?

219
00:09:29,490 --> 00:09:31,039
She's timid and weak!

220
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,439
How is that anything like me?

221
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,759
She's at least five jin heavier too!

222
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,159
Can't you tell?

223
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,209
No, wait.

224
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:36,559
Ms. Ding,

225
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,329
I'm also very confused.

226
00:09:38,330 --> 00:09:40,209
She used your phone to call me.

227
00:09:40,210 --> 00:09:41,039
This is your mess.

228
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,279
And now, you're trying to blame me?

229
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:44,439
You're pointing the finger at me?

230
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:46,329
- If it wasn't for me, this case...
- You're out of your mind!

231
00:09:46,330 --> 00:09:47,170
Hello?

232
00:09:47,640 --> 00:09:48,460
Hello?!

233
00:10:04,970 --> 00:10:06,639
I ran all the way, but I'm still late.

234
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,650
What's the word?
Did you get that bonus?

235
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:10,690
What's wrong?

236
00:10:12,610 --> 00:10:13,960
Don't scare me.

237
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,410
Talk to me.

238
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,050
There is no bonus.

239
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:20,480
My entire career is hanging by a thread.

240
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,530
Wait, what happened?

241
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,089
Look, objectively speaking,

242
00:10:28,090 --> 00:10:29,849
we're not perfect at everything.

243
00:10:29,850 --> 00:10:31,080
But,

244
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,919
when it comes to handling a crisis,

245
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:34,650
we've never backed down.

246
00:10:35,210 --> 00:10:36,530
It's okay, don't be upset.

247
00:10:37,130 --> 00:10:38,690
If it weren't for me,

248
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:41,050
her husband would've
stripped her of every cent.

249
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:42,089
Besides,

250
00:10:42,090 --> 00:10:44,009
do you have any idea
how hard I worked

251
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:45,559
just to get her trial date moved up?

252
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,410
Don't cry. It's okay.

253
00:10:49,330 --> 00:10:50,720
I'm not even upset!

254
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:52,690
I'm turning this anger into an appetite.

255
00:10:53,370 --> 00:10:55,039
We're eating to our hearts' content!

256
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,650
Waitress! Can we order?

257
00:10:57,130 --> 00:10:58,600
Sorry, hold on a second.

258
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:02,089
I just remembered something.

259
00:11:02,090 --> 00:11:02,639
Remember those

260
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:04,799
discounted groceries I mentioned?

261
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:07,360
They arrived today and are very fresh.

262
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,519
Look,

263
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:11,729
I'll head back and whip up
a feast for you.

264
00:11:11,730 --> 00:11:13,919
There's nothing a good meal can't fix.

265
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:14,759
Leave it to me.

266
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:15,639
Come on, let's go home.

267
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:16,329
No way.

268
00:11:16,330 --> 00:11:16,969
What?

269
00:11:16,970 --> 00:11:19,129
I promised to treat you
to something good.

270
00:11:19,130 --> 00:11:20,880
You think I can't afford a meal?

271
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:22,329
That's not what I meant.

272
00:11:22,330 --> 00:11:23,329
Listen,

273
00:11:23,330 --> 00:11:25,209
I was supposed
to be celebrating a win today.

274
00:11:25,210 --> 00:11:26,129
I know.

275
00:11:26,130 --> 00:11:27,279
But I still have enough

276
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:28,439
to take you out for dinner.

277
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:28,919
Waitress!

278
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:29,729
Hey, stop it.

279
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:30,799
Sorry!

280
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:31,639
Give it a rest.

281
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:35,170
I can't let you spend
your grandma's medicine money on me.

282
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:36,679
Besides,

283
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:38,209
didn't you say the other day

284
00:11:38,210 --> 00:11:40,399
that it's her birthday soon?

285
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,840
Aren't you going to see her?

286
00:11:42,250 --> 00:11:45,720
You convinced me even more
that I can't go back.

287
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:50,240
Just use the money to buy her a gift.

288
00:11:50,490 --> 00:11:52,690
We can save some travel fare.

289
00:11:53,210 --> 00:11:54,600
Look...

290
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:56,559
That's enough. Just listen to me.

291
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:58,240
Let's go home.

292
00:11:58,680 --> 00:12:00,810
Come on, let's go.

293
00:12:01,210 --> 00:12:02,450
When I make big money,

294
00:12:02,520 --> 00:12:04,519
I'll buy you something nice.

295
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:05,880
I'm holding you to that.

296
00:12:06,490 --> 00:12:08,880
Let's go. Home, now!

297
00:12:08,970 --> 00:12:10,559
Sorry, waitress!

298
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:12,960
I'll order extra cake next time!

299
00:12:18,130 --> 00:12:19,439
By the way, Xiezhi.

300
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,759
Feng Shengli's father is

301
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,760
coming tomorrow
to present a thank-you banner.

302
00:12:23,010 --> 00:12:25,329
Feng Shengli's surgery was a success,

303
00:12:25,330 --> 00:12:27,120
and he's being discharged soon.

304
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:29,129
The public has been following

305
00:12:29,130 --> 00:12:30,960
this case very closely.

306
00:12:31,730 --> 00:12:32,679
Xiezhi,

307
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:35,240
such a positive response
from the community

308
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:38,000
is all thanks to how well
you two worked together.

309
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:40,089
But more importantly,

310
00:12:40,090 --> 00:12:43,600
you truly helped those families
when they needed it most.

311
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:56,480
Morning.

312
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:04,410
Hello.

313
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:06,369
Hello, Judge.

314
00:13:06,370 --> 00:13:07,439
Judge Shen is in a hearing.

315
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:09,210
I'm the court clerk, Chen Xianghui.

316
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,450
Please, have a seat.

317
00:13:11,010 --> 00:13:12,480
I remember you.

318
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,000
Judge Chen.

319
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:16,519
When do you think
Judge Shen will be back?

320
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:17,639
Also,

321
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:18,519
when is the next hearing

322
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:20,039
for my brother's case?

323
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,279
It hasn't been set yet.

324
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:22,249
But as soon as he's back,

325
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,439
we'll get it on the schedule.

326
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,600
I see.

327
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:27,120
Could you please
mention it to Judge Shen again?

328
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,399
Our family can't afford

329
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:30,000
to let this drag on any longer.

330
00:13:30,130 --> 00:13:31,209
You have no idea

331
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:33,679
what these last ten years
have been like for us.

332
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,329
Ever since my brother was kidnapped,

333
00:13:35,330 --> 00:13:36,399
my parents gave up everything

334
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,679
just to find him.

335
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:38,720
My parents

336
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:40,639
couldn't even rest in peace

337
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:42,159
because of what happened to him.

338
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:44,439
My grandmother practically
cried herself blind.

339
00:13:44,440 --> 00:13:45,639
And now

340
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,009
our prayers have been answered.

341
00:13:47,010 --> 00:13:48,840
We've finally found him.

342
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:52,330
My grandmother and I just want
my brother back.

343
00:13:52,970 --> 00:13:54,240
Please,

344
00:13:54,330 --> 00:13:56,450
help us get a ruling soon.

345
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,720
I just want to take Guo home.

346
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:03,050
There's something I have to tell you.

347
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:05,530
Your brother's feelings

348
00:14:06,330 --> 00:14:08,080
are not quite what you think.

349
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,650
That's impossible.

350
00:14:10,970 --> 00:14:12,129
Last time he was home,

351
00:14:12,130 --> 00:14:13,729
we held each other and cried.

352
00:14:13,730 --> 00:14:16,450
He told me he wanted to come back to us!

353
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:18,720
The Qians sent over a letter.

354
00:14:19,250 --> 00:14:21,039
They say your brother wrote it himself.

355
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:22,360
Take a look.

356
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:41,090
(I'm staying with my foster parents,
Qian Zhengguo and Nie Baomei, and my sister)

357
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:51,600
No way.

358
00:14:51,610 --> 00:14:53,080
This is a fake.

359
00:14:53,250 --> 00:14:54,880
The original is right here.

360
00:14:56,530 --> 00:14:57,919
(Case File, Qingcheng District
People's Court, Tianhai City)

361
00:14:57,920 --> 00:14:59,360
I still don't believe it.

362
00:15:00,330 --> 00:15:02,720
My brother would never
write something like this.

363
00:15:03,370 --> 00:15:04,969
It has to be Qian Zhengguo
and Nie Baomei.

364
00:15:04,970 --> 00:15:06,930
Those scoundrels must have forced him.

365
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:10,089
They're just like that kidnapper, Li Gaiying.
They're all the same!

366
00:15:10,090 --> 00:15:12,240
I won't let them steal my brother away!

367
00:15:18,530 --> 00:15:20,930
(Case File, Qingcheng District
People's Court, Tianhai City)

368
00:15:26,490 --> 00:15:27,799
(Liyuan Community Service Center)

369
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:28,729
Hello.

370
00:15:28,730 --> 00:15:30,369
I need your cooperation on something.

371
00:15:30,370 --> 00:15:32,279
I'm Shen Xiezhi, a Family Court judge

372
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:34,329
of the Qingcheng District People's Court.

373
00:15:34,330 --> 00:15:35,369
I need to have a word

374
00:15:35,370 --> 00:15:37,120
with a child from your community.

375
00:15:37,250 --> 00:15:38,249
May I borrow

376
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:39,489
your meeting room?

377
00:15:39,490 --> 00:15:40,489
Let me check with my supervisor.

378
00:15:40,490 --> 00:15:41,880
Great, thank you.

379
00:15:52,730 --> 00:15:54,050
In here.

380
00:15:56,130 --> 00:15:57,810
The judge wants to see you.

381
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:59,329
Thank you.

382
00:15:59,330 --> 00:16:01,129
Hello, Judge Shen.

383
00:16:01,130 --> 00:16:03,089
Mr. Qian, Ms. Nie. We meet again.

384
00:16:03,090 --> 00:16:04,210
So...

385
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:05,759
Didn't we settle

386
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:07,799
everything in court last time?

387
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:08,329
Exactly.

388
00:16:08,330 --> 00:16:09,399
The thing is,

389
00:16:09,400 --> 00:16:10,639
it's really about Xiaosheng.

390
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,609
He just doesn't want to go back there.

391
00:16:12,610 --> 00:16:14,930
He even wrote a statement himself.

392
00:16:15,330 --> 00:16:16,279
So...

393
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:17,759
So why the second interview?

394
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:18,519
Here's the thing.

395
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:19,679
According to regulations,

396
00:16:19,680 --> 00:16:21,489
we need to have
an interview with the child.

397
00:16:21,490 --> 00:16:23,159
Another one?

398
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:24,410
Sure.

399
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,559
Xiaosheng,

400
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:27,650
it's okay.

401
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:29,089
Don't be scared.

402
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:31,279
Today, just tell Judge Shen

403
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:34,480
how you truly feel about this.

404
00:16:34,970 --> 00:16:37,969
I'm sorry, but you two need to
step out for a moment.

405
00:16:37,970 --> 00:16:40,450
We need to speak
with Xiaosheng in private.

406
00:16:41,610 --> 00:16:42,439
Step out?

407
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:44,279
What do you mean by that?

408
00:16:44,280 --> 00:16:45,799
Everything my son said is true.

409
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:46,249
Exactly.

410
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:47,369
Are you suggesting

411
00:16:47,370 --> 00:16:49,089
that we're coercing the boy?

412
00:16:49,090 --> 00:16:50,960
Yeah, what's going on here?

413
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:53,129
This is just standard
operating procedure.

414
00:16:53,130 --> 00:16:55,120
Please cooperate. Thank you.

415
00:16:55,330 --> 00:16:56,729
You can't leave him alone.

416
00:16:56,730 --> 00:16:57,679
He'll be terrified.

417
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:58,799
Mom,

418
00:16:58,800 --> 00:16:59,889
it's fine.

419
00:16:59,890 --> 00:17:01,450
I'll just talk to the judge

420
00:17:01,890 --> 00:17:02,759
for a few minutes.

421
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:03,999
It won't take long.

422
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,679
You guys head home first.

423
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:06,850
Alright, then.

424
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,849
Okay. It's fine.

425
00:17:08,850 --> 00:17:10,170
Come on, let's go.

426
00:17:10,610 --> 00:17:11,399
Alright.

427
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:12,529
Just tell him everything.

428
00:17:12,530 --> 00:17:13,679
Tell the truth.

429
00:17:13,680 --> 00:17:14,959
We're going.

430
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:15,479
Let's go.

431
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:17,480
Just stay calm, you'll be fine.

432
00:17:17,610 --> 00:17:18,769
Thank you for your cooperation.

433
00:17:18,770 --> 00:17:20,090
Just stay relaxed.

434
00:17:29,770 --> 00:17:31,800
I wrote that letter myself.

435
00:17:31,810 --> 00:17:33,089
I did it on my own.

436
00:17:33,090 --> 00:17:35,000
My parents didn't force me
into anything.

437
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:37,999
Xiaosheng,

438
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,690
if it comes down to it,

439
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:41,560
would you testify in court?

440
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,240
Would you do that?

441
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:46,000
Is that really necessary?

442
00:17:48,610 --> 00:17:49,999
Everything is in that letter.

443
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,800
I made myself perfectly clear.

444
00:17:53,370 --> 00:17:54,850
Don't you think

445
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:57,329
that if you don't show up in person

446
00:17:57,330 --> 00:17:59,040
to take a stand,

447
00:17:59,050 --> 00:18:00,760
your grandmother and sister

448
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:03,560
will never believe
those words are truly yours?

449
00:18:07,290 --> 00:18:08,560
I know

450
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:11,000
how difficult this is for you.

451
00:18:11,770 --> 00:18:13,560
I know you're only doing this

452
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:16,170
because you're angry with your sister.

453
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,329
You blame her for going after
your foster parents,

454
00:18:19,330 --> 00:18:21,890
and you want her
and your grandmother to give up

455
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,760
so they'll stop hurting your parents.

456
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:24,930
However,

457
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:28,000
if you don't show up,

458
00:18:28,770 --> 00:18:29,889
do you really think

459
00:18:29,890 --> 00:18:31,650
this is going to end that easily?

460
00:18:31,850 --> 00:18:33,930
You were gone for ten years.

461
00:18:34,610 --> 00:18:36,650
Your family gave up their entire lives.

462
00:18:37,050 --> 00:18:38,850
They never stopped looking.

463
00:18:39,290 --> 00:18:40,800
They never gave up.

464
00:18:48,090 --> 00:18:49,610
I respect your feelings.

465
00:18:50,810 --> 00:18:52,199
The parents you have now

466
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:54,240
have raised you for a decade.

467
00:18:54,920 --> 00:18:57,040
And if it's true

468
00:18:57,850 --> 00:18:59,329
that Li Gaiying told them

469
00:18:59,330 --> 00:19:00,800
you were just an abandoned baby,

470
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,760
then they are victims too.

471
00:19:05,330 --> 00:19:07,170
But whatever the truth may be,

472
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:09,329
your grandmother and sister

473
00:19:09,330 --> 00:19:11,610
are without a doubt
victims in all of this.

474
00:19:12,130 --> 00:19:13,720
In their search for you,

475
00:19:13,890 --> 00:19:15,760
they already gave up everything.

476
00:19:18,570 --> 00:19:20,000
If you can,

477
00:19:21,850 --> 00:19:23,999
maybe you should meet them

478
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,210
and tell them yourself.

479
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:28,130
Tell them what you're really thinking.

480
00:19:28,810 --> 00:19:30,410
Tell them that you want to stay,

481
00:19:30,770 --> 00:19:32,320
but that you're also willing

482
00:19:32,530 --> 00:19:34,650
to stay in regular contact with them.

483
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:37,090
It's better than just

484
00:19:37,290 --> 00:19:38,690
hiding from them

485
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,800
and leaving them in despair.

486
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:50,210
Judge.

487
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:52,650
I'll do as you say.

488
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:56,040
I'll tell them in court.

489
00:19:59,770 --> 00:20:00,929
Good.

490
00:20:00,930 --> 00:20:03,490
(Serving the People is My Mission)

491
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,369
That kid has had it rough.

492
00:20:06,370 --> 00:20:08,320
An adult would be reeling in his shoes.

493
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:09,999
Never mind that Li Gaiying insists

494
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,569
the child is dead.

495
00:20:11,570 --> 00:20:14,720
The Qians also can prove that
they adopted the boy legally.

496
00:20:14,890 --> 00:20:16,450
after ten years of raising the boy,

497
00:20:16,530 --> 00:20:18,809
can you really just erase that?

498
00:20:18,810 --> 00:20:21,370
There's no need to trade places.

499
00:20:21,850 --> 00:20:23,479
That kid's life was doomed
to be a tragedy

500
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:25,760
from the moment that nanny took him.

501
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:28,849
If he'd ended up with monsters,

502
00:20:28,850 --> 00:20:30,850
he wouldn't be so conflicted today.

503
00:20:31,130 --> 00:20:32,399
But a childhood like that

504
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:34,329
leaves a lifelong shadow.

505
00:20:34,330 --> 00:20:35,289
With foster parents

506
00:20:35,290 --> 00:20:37,370
who love him like their own,

507
00:20:37,890 --> 00:20:39,569
he's forced to spend his life

508
00:20:39,570 --> 00:20:41,199
torn between love and hate.

509
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,890
Wait, are you saying

510
00:20:43,050 --> 00:20:45,329
the Qians might have known
they were buying him?

511
00:20:45,330 --> 00:20:46,720
Presumption of innocence.

512
00:20:46,810 --> 00:20:48,720
Until we have certain evidence,

513
00:20:49,130 --> 00:20:50,690
I'm not making that claim.

514
00:20:53,850 --> 00:20:55,170
Judge Shen.

515
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,919
Let's not be so formal.

516
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,049
I'm telling you,

517
00:20:58,050 --> 00:20:59,690
it just feels wrong.

518
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:01,479
We see too many complicated cases.

519
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:02,439
With emotion on one side,

520
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:04,089
and logic on the other, it's tormenting.

521
00:21:04,090 --> 00:21:05,369
And the boy is so young.

522
00:21:05,370 --> 00:21:06,760
It's too much to ask of him.

523
00:21:06,770 --> 00:21:07,849
Alright, that's enough.

524
00:21:07,850 --> 00:21:08,999
We should stop now.

525
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:10,129
If we keep going,

526
00:21:10,130 --> 00:21:12,320
I won't be able to stay objective
about this case.

527
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:20,199
Welcome.

528
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,800
- Jing.
- Come in.

529
00:21:21,810 --> 00:21:23,129
Should we change shoes?

530
00:21:23,130 --> 00:21:24,199
Don't worry about it.

531
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,560
Really?

532
00:21:25,570 --> 00:21:26,199
Come on in.

533
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:28,000
You brought so much stuff!

534
00:21:33,090 --> 00:21:35,369
It's from my cousin.

535
00:21:35,370 --> 00:21:37,889
She's on a huge decluttering kick

536
00:21:37,890 --> 00:21:38,959
and sent over these things

537
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:41,090
her kids outgrew.

538
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:43,609
Since we aren't even expecting yet,

539
00:21:43,610 --> 00:21:45,560
I figured Fei could play with them.

540
00:21:47,890 --> 00:21:49,130
Where is Fei?

541
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:58,960
She's okay.

542
00:21:59,480 --> 00:22:00,959
Look at all these books.

543
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:02,720
She's such a bookworm.

544
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:04,960
She'll come out to see them in a bit.

545
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:09,720
Fei?

546
00:22:11,810 --> 00:22:13,130
Fei!

547
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:43,089
Last year, I missed the trip

548
00:22:43,090 --> 00:22:45,520
because I was sick.

549
00:22:45,530 --> 00:22:46,889
And the year before,

550
00:22:46,890 --> 00:22:48,610
it was that interview, right?

551
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,639
No, that wasn't it.

552
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:52,760
I think that was three years ago.

553
00:22:53,720 --> 00:22:56,000
What happened the year before last?

554
00:22:56,090 --> 00:22:57,890
That year...

555
00:22:59,090 --> 00:23:00,959
I was busy feeding strays.

556
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:03,289
It was because of the dogs, remember?

557
00:23:03,290 --> 00:23:04,809
Your client claimed

558
00:23:04,810 --> 00:23:06,159
there was an emergency,

559
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:08,280
but she just had three dogs
with no sitter.

560
00:23:08,330 --> 00:23:09,089
And you said,

561
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:10,919
"This is my first big case."

562
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:12,089
You were so desperate that

563
00:23:12,090 --> 00:23:14,000
you were even willing to dog-sit.

564
00:23:14,370 --> 00:23:16,890
Okay, don't mention the dogs again.

565
00:23:17,200 --> 00:23:19,609
That woman was
the Waterloo of my career.

566
00:23:19,610 --> 00:23:20,329
I'm serious.

567
00:23:20,330 --> 00:23:22,890
Bring up the dogs again
and I'll bite you.

568
00:23:24,290 --> 00:23:25,650
Exactly my point.

569
00:23:25,850 --> 00:23:27,889
Ms. Ding firing you now

570
00:23:27,890 --> 00:23:29,809
must be a sign from above.

571
00:23:29,810 --> 00:23:30,809
You've missed your grandma's

572
00:23:30,810 --> 00:23:32,480
birthday every year.

573
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:35,370
Let's see
what excuse you find this time.

574
00:23:37,570 --> 00:23:40,280
I'll give it some thought.

575
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:41,960
I have to go.

576
00:23:50,570 --> 00:23:53,410
(Grandma:
Xiang, have you been busy lately?)

577
00:23:53,610 --> 00:23:55,479
(Don't just focus on making money.)

578
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:58,090
(Eat well and take care of yourself.)

579
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:00,090
(I only have 600 yuan left.)

580
00:24:00,130 --> 00:24:02,210
(That won't even
cover my expenses this month.)

581
00:24:02,570 --> 00:24:04,210
(How am I supposed to go home?)

582
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:12,040
(I'm so sorry, Grandma.)

583
00:24:12,610 --> 00:24:13,919
(I won't be able to make it back)

584
00:24:13,920 --> 00:24:15,520
(for your birthday this year.)

585
00:24:15,570 --> 00:24:16,650
(Work is going great.)

586
00:24:16,850 --> 00:24:18,520
(I just landed a massive case.)

587
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,090
(Once I'm done with this, I'll...)

588
00:24:20,890 --> 00:24:22,479
(Grandma: Don't worry about coming home.)

589
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:24,399
(Just get some rest when you can.)

590
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:27,129
(I've been feeling much better lately.)

591
00:24:27,130 --> 00:24:28,450
(Don't you worry about me.)

592
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:45,090
(I love you, Grandma.)

593
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:47,040
(Thank you.)

594
00:24:47,330 --> 00:24:49,690
(I hope you live to be a hundred.)

595
00:25:13,090 --> 00:25:15,280
I've got your numbers down, ladies.

596
00:25:15,370 --> 00:25:16,089
I'll give you a call

597
00:25:16,090 --> 00:25:17,439
as soon as I'm back at the office.

598
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,329
Here,

599
00:25:18,330 --> 00:25:19,760
take a sausage.

600
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:22,159
Free consultations come with a snack!

601
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,800
But to get a real sausage,

602
00:25:23,810 --> 00:25:25,849
you have to bring me a valid lead.

603
00:25:25,850 --> 00:25:28,000
Any potential case for me?

604
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,210
How about you, sir?

605
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:31,609
Are these even edible?

606
00:25:31,610 --> 00:25:32,889
They look so cheap.

607
00:25:32,890 --> 00:25:34,049
Here, boy!

608
00:25:34,050 --> 00:25:35,439
Ugh, even the dog won't eat it. Toss it.

609
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:36,890
Just throw it away.

610
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:40,850
He's short on cash for a new car.

611
00:25:40,890 --> 00:25:42,480
He wants me to lend him 50,000 yuan.

612
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:44,159
You haven't gotten yours?

613
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,159
Here,

614
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:45,809
take this.

615
00:25:45,810 --> 00:25:46,679
Thanks.

616
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:48,800
Talk about a spending downgrade.

617
00:25:48,960 --> 00:25:50,609
These sausages are high quality!

618
00:25:50,610 --> 00:25:52,329
They're firm and full of nutrients.

619
00:25:52,330 --> 00:25:53,760
Watch, I'll eat one.

620
00:25:54,050 --> 00:25:55,479
See? Perfectly fine.

621
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:56,159
Here.

622
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:57,329
If you have a real lead,

623
00:25:57,330 --> 00:25:58,439
just give me a call.

624
00:25:58,440 --> 00:25:59,800
My number is right here.

625
00:26:06,450 --> 00:26:08,329
(Plaintiff)

626
00:26:08,330 --> 00:26:10,410
(Defendante)

627
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:12,370
Is Guo coming today?

628
00:26:12,570 --> 00:26:14,760
Are they even bringing him here?

629
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:16,370
It's okay. Don't worry.

630
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:19,289
Look at them.

631
00:26:19,290 --> 00:26:20,959
What a great performance.

632
00:26:20,960 --> 00:26:22,890
We're clearly the victims here.

633
00:26:27,890 --> 00:26:29,130
Calm down.

634
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:32,450
Try to stay calm.
There's no reason to be nervous.

635
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:35,850
Once we finish here today,

636
00:26:36,890 --> 00:26:38,890
we're finally taking my brother home.

637
00:26:42,490 --> 00:26:43,849
(Children's Room, In Use)

638
00:26:43,850 --> 00:26:46,289
Your Honor, Court Clerk,

639
00:26:46,290 --> 00:26:47,850
and to my dear family.

640
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:50,720
You are all gathered here today
because of me,

641
00:26:50,850 --> 00:26:52,129
and because of

642
00:26:52,130 --> 00:26:54,239
a mistake made ten years ago.

643
00:26:54,240 --> 00:26:55,329
For the last decade,

644
00:26:55,330 --> 00:26:57,719
my family has paid an unimaginable price

645
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:00,089
just to find me.

646
00:27:00,090 --> 00:27:01,049
Moving forward,

647
00:27:01,050 --> 00:27:03,690
I want to fulfill my duties as a son

648
00:27:03,850 --> 00:27:05,130
and honor you.

649
00:27:15,330 --> 00:27:17,210
The court will now come to order.

650
00:27:18,610 --> 00:27:20,000
Over these past ten years,

651
00:27:20,400 --> 00:27:22,439
my foster parents have
done everything possible

652
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:25,609
to provide me
with the best life and education.

653
00:27:25,610 --> 00:27:27,159
They raised and taught me

654
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:29,370
with the deepest love.

655
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,850
Their love for me

656
00:27:30,890 --> 00:27:33,650
is no different
than that of any other parent.

657
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:34,609
It is my wish

658
00:27:34,610 --> 00:27:37,280
that I may continue to live
with my foster parents,

659
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:39,889
Qian Zhengguo and Nie Baomei.

660
00:27:39,890 --> 00:27:42,889
I want to continue my life
in the environment I know.

661
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:43,849
But this doesn't mean

662
00:27:43,850 --> 00:27:45,930
I am turning my back
on our blood bond.

663
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,719
I will still fulfill my responsibilities

664
00:27:47,720 --> 00:27:49,439
and duties as a grandson.

665
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:52,369
I only hope that we can
let go of past hatred

666
00:27:52,370 --> 00:27:54,650
and find a way
to live our lives together.

667
00:27:55,570 --> 00:27:58,450
And find a way
to live our lives together...

668
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:00,480
Young man?

669
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:02,610
It's time to go in.

670
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:11,439
Don't be afraid.

671
00:28:11,440 --> 00:28:13,159
Everyone in there is your family.

672
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:15,280
Just say exactly what's in your heart.

673
00:28:18,290 --> 00:28:19,919
The Panel Judges are entering the court.

674
00:28:19,920 --> 00:28:21,450
All rise.

675
00:28:36,720 --> 00:28:37,800
Please be seated.

676
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,170
Court is now in session.

677
00:28:43,570 --> 00:28:45,250
(Court in session)

678
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:57,769
Xiaosheng...

679
00:28:57,770 --> 00:28:58,960
Guo...

680
00:28:59,890 --> 00:29:01,170
Son...

681
00:29:12,290 --> 00:29:13,410
It's okay.

682
00:29:15,290 --> 00:29:16,480
Guo...

683
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:22,170
Don't be afraid.

684
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:26,130
Witness, please take a seat.

685
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:31,520
Witness Qian Xiaosheng,

686
00:29:31,770 --> 00:29:33,320
you may begin your statement.

687
00:29:33,890 --> 00:29:34,919
Judge,

688
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:36,890
may I say a few words to him first?

689
00:29:38,330 --> 00:29:39,239
Judge,

690
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,690
recently,

691
00:29:40,890 --> 00:29:42,850
they haven't let us
see my brother at all.

692
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:44,849
They're probably brainwashing him.

693
00:29:44,850 --> 00:29:45,639
This...

694
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:47,329
- How can you say that?
- That's uncalled for!

695
00:29:47,330 --> 00:29:49,889
Just let my grandmother
say a few words to him.

696
00:29:49,890 --> 00:29:50,960
Please?

697
00:29:53,050 --> 00:29:54,240
Does the defendant

698
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:55,690
have any objections?

699
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:58,089
No objection. Let her speak.

700
00:29:58,090 --> 00:29:59,439
- Go ahead.
- Why are we letting her speak?

701
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:00,569
Plaintiff,

702
00:30:00,570 --> 00:30:01,760
proceed.

703
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:03,809
It's okay. Keep it brief.

704
00:30:03,810 --> 00:30:05,650
Focus on the important part.
Don't be nervous.

705
00:30:05,810 --> 00:30:07,090
Guo...

706
00:30:10,640 --> 00:30:12,000
You must remember...

707
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:15,560
Your sister and I,

708
00:30:15,610 --> 00:30:17,650
and your parents in heaven,

709
00:30:18,290 --> 00:30:20,450
will always love you.

710
00:30:22,920 --> 00:30:26,760
♪Happy birthday to you♪

711
00:30:26,890 --> 00:30:31,450
♪Happy birthday to you♪

712
00:30:31,570 --> 00:30:36,240
♪Happy birthday to you♪

713
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:39,890
Okay?

714
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:45,650
Xiaosheng,

715
00:30:46,610 --> 00:30:49,040
Mom and Dad love you, too.

716
00:30:51,570 --> 00:30:52,720
Qian Xiaosheng,

717
00:30:53,330 --> 00:30:54,760
please continue.

718
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:01,130
Presiding Judge,

719
00:31:01,850 --> 00:31:03,170
court clerk,

720
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:05,690
dear parents.

721
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:08,930
I am...

722
00:31:12,290 --> 00:31:13,520
I...

723
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,130
I am...

724
00:31:16,240 --> 00:31:18,520
I...

725
00:31:26,570 --> 00:31:28,040
I'm sorry, Judge.

726
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:29,960
Son!

727
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:30,569
Guo!

728
00:31:30,570 --> 00:31:32,040
- Xiaosheng!
- Son!

729
00:31:32,130 --> 00:31:33,089
- Guo!
- Son!

730
00:31:33,090 --> 00:31:34,370
Xiaosheng!

731
00:31:37,370 --> 00:31:38,690
Son...

732
00:31:57,810 --> 00:31:58,889
I've been trying to call,

733
00:31:58,890 --> 00:32:00,529
but the Qians aren't picking up.

734
00:32:00,530 --> 00:32:01,329
I called the police station

735
00:32:01,330 --> 00:32:02,690
where they're registered.

736
00:32:02,770 --> 00:32:03,959
Based on the ticket records

737
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,439
linked to their ID numbers,

738
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:06,479
they've returned to Qian Village.

739
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:07,889
All three of them went back together.

740
00:32:07,890 --> 00:32:09,320
Here are the ticket records.

741
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,480
That was fast.

742
00:32:13,770 --> 00:32:15,520
Heading home right after court?

743
00:32:15,770 --> 00:32:17,199
Well, after all that ordeal,

744
00:32:17,200 --> 00:32:18,129
maybe going home

745
00:32:18,130 --> 00:32:19,890
holds a special meaning for them.

746
00:32:33,010 --> 00:32:36,679
(Qian Zhengguo,No. 18 of Qian Village,
Baimao Town, Wuwei City, Huaiqing)

747
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:38,130
Baimao Town?

748
00:32:42,210 --> 00:32:43,009
(Divorce Dispute:
Ding Yajing vs. Cheng Kuiyuan)

749
00:32:43,010 --> 00:32:46,490
(Qin Rui, 20 Outang Village,
Baimao Town, Wuwei City, Huaiqing)

750
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:51,439
Five minutes left!

751
00:32:51,440 --> 00:32:53,720
Free giveaway!

752
00:32:53,850 --> 00:32:55,369
Legal consultations, free of charge!

753
00:32:55,370 --> 00:32:57,480
Plus a free carton of milk.

754
00:32:57,640 --> 00:33:00,369
Does anyone else need legal advice?

755
00:33:00,370 --> 00:33:02,720
Come sign up right here.

756
00:33:10,050 --> 00:33:11,479
I can't let you spend

757
00:33:11,480 --> 00:33:12,889
your grandma's
medicine money on me.

758
00:33:12,890 --> 00:33:14,399
Didn't you say the other day

759
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:16,610
that it's her birthday soon?

760
00:33:17,610 --> 00:33:21,000
You convinced me even more
that I can't go back.

761
00:33:25,490 --> 00:33:27,090
(Senior Lawyer,
Professional Consultation)

762
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:40,090
Thank you.

763
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:51,719
Judge Shen.

764
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:53,369
I'm actually here on business.

765
00:33:53,370 --> 00:33:54,919
I'm not stalking you.

766
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:56,769
I was actually looking for you.

767
00:33:56,770 --> 00:33:57,960
Me?

768
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:01,960
Do you have any plans to head home soon?

769
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:03,410
To your hometown?

770
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:07,120
I was going to,

771
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:09,250
but things have been so crazy lately.

772
00:34:09,290 --> 00:34:10,530
I doubt

773
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:12,170
I'll have time.

774
00:34:12,290 --> 00:34:13,760
Work's just too much.

775
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:15,210
Busy handing out flyers?

776
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:16,889
What's that supposed to mean?

777
00:34:16,890 --> 00:34:19,320
My job is none of your concern.

778
00:34:20,690 --> 00:34:22,320
It was actually a coincidence.

779
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:24,769
If you'd passed by at noon,

780
00:34:24,770 --> 00:34:25,369
I would've...

781
00:34:25,370 --> 00:34:26,519
If I'd passed by at noon,

782
00:34:26,520 --> 00:34:28,280
you'd have seen me
at the court gates.

783
00:34:28,850 --> 00:34:30,479
Forget it, you wouldn't understand.

784
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:32,130
You're just that kind of person.

785
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:33,919
I really need to speak with you.

786
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:35,320
Put those down first.

787
00:34:38,690 --> 00:34:40,720
Can you send me your ID number?

788
00:34:40,730 --> 00:34:42,130
My ID number?

789
00:34:42,370 --> 00:34:43,119
What for?

790
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:44,559
I've given you plenty of case files.

791
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:45,689
It's all in there.

792
00:34:45,690 --> 00:34:47,400
I need your consent first.

793
00:34:49,730 --> 00:34:50,769
I'd like to buy you

794
00:34:50,770 --> 00:34:52,800
one of those unlimited flight passes.

795
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,439
It's good for six months.

796
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:55,689
That way,

797
00:34:55,690 --> 00:34:57,439
whenever you want to go home

798
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:59,289
to your hometown, you can.

799
00:34:59,290 --> 00:35:00,920
Buying me a plane ticket?

800
00:35:01,210 --> 00:35:02,610
What's this about?

801
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:05,570
You're a judge,

802
00:35:05,810 --> 00:35:08,209
and I'm a lawyer. This isn't right.

803
00:35:08,210 --> 00:35:10,119
There might be cameras around.

804
00:35:10,120 --> 00:35:12,599
I don't want people
getting the wrong idea.

805
00:35:12,600 --> 00:35:14,920
If you're going
to be that pedantic about it...

806
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:18,570
What about back at the fire,

807
00:35:18,770 --> 00:35:20,849
when you helped me save Fei?

808
00:35:20,850 --> 00:35:22,959
Trading a few tickets for a life?

809
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:24,210
Hardly crossing a line.

810
00:35:26,040 --> 00:35:28,530
Don't be so dramatic.

811
00:35:28,650 --> 00:35:30,650
Helping you back then

812
00:35:30,740 --> 00:35:31,919
was just about survival.

813
00:35:31,920 --> 00:35:34,079
It wasn't a big deal.

814
00:35:34,080 --> 00:35:35,920
Besides, you've saved me before, too.

815
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:38,039
Does all this back-and-forth
really matter?

816
00:35:38,040 --> 00:35:38,689
Is this important,

817
00:35:38,690 --> 00:35:40,970
or is your grandmother's
birthday important?

818
00:35:44,170 --> 00:35:45,689
Fine. It's settled.

819
00:35:45,690 --> 00:35:47,010
I'm getting the pass.

820
00:35:49,170 --> 00:35:50,760
Just don't let it go to waste.

821
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:53,280
(How did he even know?)

822
00:35:54,420 --> 00:36:00,930
♪Lean on my tender shoulder♪

823
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:03,369
Judge Shen!

824
00:36:03,370 --> 00:36:04,720
Thank you!

825
00:36:05,770 --> 00:36:07,369
When I'm making the big bucks,

826
00:36:07,370 --> 00:36:08,759
I'll definitely pay you back.

827
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:15,170
♪I'll be there for you
until the very end♪

828
00:36:28,370 --> 00:36:29,770
(Standing for the Law,
Protecting Your Rights)

829
00:36:29,810 --> 00:36:30,930
(Rui's Legal Lens is Live)

830
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:33,729
Is this a total loss of humanity,

831
00:36:33,730 --> 00:36:35,559
or just a collapse of moral values?

832
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:37,090
Let's find out together on

833
00:36:37,250 --> 00:36:38,690
Rui's Legal Lens.

834
00:36:38,730 --> 00:36:39,479
To my regular fans,

835
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:40,769
you already know

836
00:36:40,770 --> 00:36:42,439
that I usually handle

837
00:36:42,440 --> 00:36:43,889
international legal disputes

838
00:36:43,890 --> 00:36:45,329
that are very high-stakes.

839
00:36:45,330 --> 00:36:47,369
I actually just hopped off a flight,

840
00:36:47,370 --> 00:36:49,760
so I'm still battling
some serious jet lag.

841
00:36:51,770 --> 00:36:54,079
Aren't you laying it on a bit thick?

842
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:56,369
The video is only a few minutes long,

843
00:36:56,370 --> 00:36:58,490
and the intro was pure fiction.

844
00:36:58,810 --> 00:37:01,010
Hey, that was all carefully staged.

845
00:37:01,170 --> 00:37:03,170
I think it adds some flavor.

846
00:37:03,770 --> 00:37:05,320
Let me give you some advice.

847
00:37:05,690 --> 00:37:06,329
You should put

848
00:37:06,330 --> 00:37:08,440
a polished headshot at the start.

849
00:37:09,170 --> 00:37:12,760
"A beautiful lawyer leads you
into the legal world."

850
00:37:13,120 --> 00:37:14,809
The views would be huge.

851
00:37:14,810 --> 00:37:15,999
At that rate,

852
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:17,479
I might as well wear a bikini,

853
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:19,800
a sun hat, and some sunglasses too.

854
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:21,729
Polished photos?

855
00:37:21,730 --> 00:37:23,169
Give me a break.

856
00:37:23,170 --> 00:37:24,889
I let my talent do the talking.

857
00:37:24,890 --> 00:37:26,530
My brand is all about professionalism.

858
00:37:26,730 --> 00:37:28,490
Fine, fine.

859
00:37:28,560 --> 00:37:30,369
Our respected Ms. Qin
doesn't take shortcuts.

860
00:37:30,370 --> 00:37:31,690
Okay?

861
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:37,010
Snarky Lawyer?

862
00:37:38,690 --> 00:37:40,959
Wait, is this the Snarky Lawyer

863
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:42,369
who was trending a while back?

864
00:37:42,370 --> 00:37:43,479
What's up?

865
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:45,240
Is there some new scandal?

866
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:46,840
He followed you.

867
00:37:47,330 --> 00:37:48,650
Followed me?

868
00:37:48,770 --> 00:37:50,010
No way.

869
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:51,209
It's probably a fake account

870
00:37:51,210 --> 00:37:53,769
with an underscore
or a space in the name.

871
00:37:53,770 --> 00:37:55,329
The real guy would never follow me.

872
00:37:55,330 --> 00:37:57,650
Even though I've followed him for ages.

873
00:37:58,210 --> 00:38:00,039
It's real! Not an imposter.

874
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:01,840
See for yourself. Look!

875
00:38:03,050 --> 00:38:04,249
(The Snarky Lawyer)

876
00:38:04,250 --> 00:38:06,530
(Legal Outreach)

877
00:38:08,690 --> 00:38:09,880
Oh my!

878
00:38:11,600 --> 00:38:12,689
It really is him.

879
00:38:12,690 --> 00:38:15,210
A million-follower influencer
just followed me!

880
00:38:17,370 --> 00:38:18,880
I must be dreaming.

881
00:38:19,850 --> 00:38:21,760
Am I going to get tons of new followers?

882
00:38:22,080 --> 00:38:24,119
Maybe we can do
a joint livestream later.

883
00:38:24,120 --> 00:38:25,289
Create some buzz.

884
00:38:25,290 --> 00:38:27,090
I might actually go viral!

885
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,959
I could make a living off social media.

886
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:32,209
Think of the ad revenue!

887
00:38:32,210 --> 00:38:33,289
I'd be rolling in money!

888
00:38:33,290 --> 00:38:34,559
Exactly.

889
00:38:34,560 --> 00:38:35,599
You'd be rich.

890
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:37,650
He really followed me.

891
00:38:37,810 --> 00:38:40,050
I'm going to ride your coattails now.

892
00:38:40,210 --> 00:38:41,650
It's really him.

893
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:47,610
I've been shown
a lot of kindness lately.

894
00:38:48,080 --> 00:38:50,800
It looks like our luck
is finally turning around.

895
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:53,760
This is great.

896
00:39:02,080 --> 00:39:03,400
I'm home!

897
00:39:03,650 --> 00:39:04,970
Welcome back.

898
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:07,320
Come here and help us wrap dumplings.

899
00:39:09,810 --> 00:39:12,090
What's the occasion? Why dumplings?

900
00:39:12,250 --> 00:39:13,369
What's the filling?

901
00:39:13,370 --> 00:39:14,689
Three-delicacies filling.

902
00:39:14,690 --> 00:39:16,209
Dumplings for the road,
noodles for the welcome.

903
00:39:16,210 --> 00:39:17,970
It's a procedure we can't skip.

904
00:39:18,080 --> 00:39:19,329
I'm only gone for a few days.

905
00:39:19,330 --> 00:39:21,689
There's no need to make such a fuss.

906
00:39:21,690 --> 00:39:23,130
Exactly what I said.

907
00:39:23,290 --> 00:39:25,050
A total waste of energy.

908
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:28,439
Waste of energy, maybe, but not money.

909
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:28,999
Besides,

910
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:31,479
staying busy helps prevent dementia.

911
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:33,050
I don't need to worry about that.

912
00:39:33,330 --> 00:39:35,880
Between lesson plans and teaching,

913
00:39:36,250 --> 00:39:37,440
my brain

914
00:39:37,730 --> 00:39:39,650
is doing just fine, trust me.

915
00:39:39,730 --> 00:39:40,369
Good to know.

916
00:39:40,370 --> 00:39:43,280
So, who's going on this trip with you?

917
00:39:44,250 --> 00:39:45,439
Is it Xianghui?

918
00:39:45,440 --> 00:39:47,889
Should we invite him over for dumplings?

919
00:39:47,890 --> 00:39:49,729
He's not going. I'm going alone.

920
00:39:49,730 --> 00:39:52,369
The court is only sending you?

921
00:39:52,370 --> 00:39:53,649
No one else?

922
00:39:53,650 --> 00:39:54,769
No need.

923
00:39:54,770 --> 00:39:57,090
Local colleagues will be assisting me.

924
00:39:57,440 --> 00:39:58,650
Listen,

925
00:39:58,850 --> 00:40:00,400
even as a Chief Physician

926
00:40:01,210 --> 00:40:02,599
who's hit middle age,

927
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:05,050
you shouldn't let your standards slip.

928
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:06,369
When have I ever

929
00:40:06,370 --> 00:40:08,169
let my standards slip?

930
00:40:08,170 --> 00:40:09,329
What Dad means is,

931
00:40:09,330 --> 00:40:12,440
stop meddling
and asking so many questions.

932
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:15,209
What's the deal with you two?

933
00:40:15,210 --> 00:40:16,559
Dad, look at them.

934
00:40:16,560 --> 00:40:18,490
They're ganging up on me!

935
00:40:19,290 --> 00:40:20,889
This is a family feud.

936
00:40:20,890 --> 00:40:21,999
Don't involve the innocent.

937
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:23,329
I'm a civilian.

938
00:40:23,330 --> 00:40:25,440
I'm protected by the Geneva Convention!

939
00:40:26,890 --> 00:40:29,889
(Home is meant to be our sanctuary,)

940
00:40:29,890 --> 00:40:31,689
(our place of comfort.)

941
00:40:31,690 --> 00:40:33,010
(But going home)

942
00:40:33,290 --> 00:40:34,519
(can sometimes feel overwhelming)

943
00:40:34,520 --> 00:40:38,650
(for those who are truly weary.)

944
00:40:39,290 --> 00:40:40,649
(Once upon a time,)

945
00:40:40,650 --> 00:40:43,490
(I couldn't really
grasp that complexity.)

946
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:45,399
(I had that academic arrogance,)

947
00:40:45,400 --> 00:40:46,999
(even silently resenting my father)

948
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:49,079
(for being so hard on me.)

949
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:51,090
(It wasn't until
I joined the Family Court,)

950
00:40:51,370 --> 00:40:52,649
(until I was)

951
00:40:52,650 --> 00:40:54,039
(listening day after day)

952
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:56,800
(to stories soaked in tears,)

953
00:40:57,290 --> 00:40:59,610
(that I finally understood his intent.)

954
00:41:00,120 --> 00:41:01,769
(He wanted me to touch)

955
00:41:01,770 --> 00:41:05,610
(the rawest, most authentic
marks of life.)

956
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:08,320
(The old me, who lived in a bubble,)

957
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:10,800
(finally touched the ground.)

958
00:41:11,730 --> 00:41:13,119
(As judges,)

959
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:14,530
(perhaps all we can do)

960
00:41:14,730 --> 00:41:16,399
(is strive to create moments)

961
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:18,919
(where both sides can open up)

962
00:41:18,920 --> 00:41:20,920
(and talk sincerely.)

963
00:41:21,080 --> 00:41:21,959
(To protect every)

964
00:41:21,960 --> 00:41:24,400
(hard-won family reunion.)

965
00:41:25,250 --> 00:41:26,559
(This realization)

966
00:41:26,560 --> 00:41:27,729
(quietly melted the silence)

967
00:41:27,730 --> 00:41:28,849
(between my father and me)

968
00:41:28,850 --> 00:41:31,090
(that had lasted for so long.)

969
00:41:31,370 --> 00:41:33,240
(When I finally sat down)

970
00:41:33,250 --> 00:41:34,959
(and started listening to him)

971
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:36,440
(just as I listened to my clients,)

972
00:41:36,810 --> 00:41:40,010
(I saw beneath his clumsy concern)

973
00:41:40,290 --> 00:41:41,849
(the same core)

974
00:41:41,850 --> 00:41:44,970
(as what I am doing now.)

975
00:41:45,600 --> 00:41:48,360
(A stubborn, steadfast protection.)

976
00:41:48,520 --> 00:41:49,599
(It turns out)

977
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:52,320
(that while helping others
find their way,)

978
00:41:52,690 --> 00:41:55,360
(I also found my own way home.)

979
00:42:02,210 --> 00:42:03,610
(After 11 years, Liu Hongying's son,
Yuan Guoguo, has finally been found.)

980
00:42:21,370 --> 00:42:22,800
Judge Shen?

981
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:24,610
What a coincidence.

982
00:42:25,080 --> 00:42:26,610
Are you going to Wuwei City too?

983
00:42:26,690 --> 00:42:28,320
Yeah. Business trip.

984
00:42:29,080 --> 00:42:30,399
I didn't expect you

985
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:31,649
to use your flight pass today.

986
00:42:31,650 --> 00:42:33,329
There's only one flight a week.

987
00:42:33,330 --> 00:42:35,170
I wanted to see Grandma early.

988
00:42:37,440 --> 00:42:39,800
You're going to investigate
the Xiaosheng case, aren't you?

989
00:42:41,890 --> 00:42:43,249
Don't try to hide it.

990
00:42:43,250 --> 00:42:44,399
When Xiaosheng's

991
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:45,729
DNA results came out,

992
00:42:45,730 --> 00:42:47,729
it went viral all over the internet.

993
00:42:47,730 --> 00:42:48,849
Even my hometown chat groups

994
00:42:48,850 --> 00:42:50,570
were buzzing about it.

995
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:53,959
Do you live in Qian Village too?

996
00:42:53,960 --> 00:42:54,439
No.

997
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:57,010
I'm in Outang Village right next to it.
Very close.

998
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:00,530
Are you going alone?

999
00:43:01,210 --> 00:43:01,919
Yes.

1000
00:43:01,920 --> 00:43:04,210
How about this? I'll be your guide.

1001
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1002
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1003
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1004
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1005
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1006
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1007
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1008
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1009
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1010
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1011
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1012
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1013
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1014
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1015
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1016
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1017
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1018
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1019
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1020
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1021
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1022
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1023
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1024
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1025
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1026
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1027
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1028
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1029
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

1030
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

1031
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1032
00:45:03,120 --> 00:45:07,130
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1033
00:45:07,310 --> 00:45:12,360
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1034
00:45:12,730 --> 00:45:16,430
♪Where fairness stands♪

1035
00:45:16,600 --> 00:45:19,680
♪Within the law♪

1036
00:45:20,840 --> 00:45:29,520
♪And within every heart♪
